D.q[1195] = "Hmm, I see, Oto Mustam sent you to get the report back...\nPerfect timing! I\'ve just finished it. I hope it will come in handy for you. I can\'t wait for the streets of the city to darken...";
D.q[2024] = "Baamm...Yes, that\'s right! Look at my strength... I\'m getting more powerful. Don\'t forget: in a fight, throw your punishment spells before receiving any blow, and you\'ll feel your strength boiling up inside you!";
D.q[8106] = "";
D.q[7147] = "";
D.q[6288] = "How did the jewel disappear? You wouldn\'t have put it in a safe box and hidden it in a grave in Brakmar Cemetery, making a pact with Chafers to look after it while you were gone by any chance? Unless you tossed it off to Jiaye Djaul for a handful of Kamas. I don\'t believe you. I\'ve seen you hanging around that black marketeer and it wouldn\'t surprise me one bit if I found out the two of you were in business together. Bring me the jewel or I\'ll get Sbab to make sausages out of your intestines.";
D.q[8107] = "";
D.q[8108] = "";
D.q[7127] = "";
D.q[744] = "We need people to help with the extension of the militia building. I\'ve two jobs to offer you. Choose one and I\'ll assign the other to Torche.\nIf you think you have the soul of a Lumberjack, we need 20 Ash planks to make the floor.\nIf not, and you want more action, I need 10 Treechnid roots to hold the beams together.";
D.q[4234] = "We\'ve named it Plasmogrine, and we now know it\'s self-aware, a frightening thought indeed. This primitive form of the organism has given us a deep insight into the mysteries of evolution... Our discoveries cast doubt over the very stability of the world!\nIf only Otomai had not taken this so far. I can tell you his intentions were not evil.";
D.q[5270] = "How do you think the battle is going?";
D.q[5236] = "";
D.q[5871] = "";
D.q[8109] = "";
D.q[1271] = "How dreadful! Next time clean the items before you bring them to me!";
D.q[6577] = "We get a lot of tacticians in the library, because we\'ve many books on the subject. There\'s one tactician in particular who\'s been coming here for the past 30 years or so to study. Gomery Mont is his name, an Enutrof. Unfortunately, he got it into his head to visit the Skeleton Dungeon to practice his profession. I say unfortunately because he was meant to come back more than a week ago and we still haven\'t heard a thing from him. Something must have gone wrong.";
D.q[5092] = "";
D.q[7227] = "";
D.q[7105] = "";
D.q[4440] = "Shhhh! Are you here to bring us poison?";
D.q[5874] = "";
D.q[5244] = "";
D.q[6165] = "We found many troubling signs during our long archaeological excavations on the island. This ancient civilisation left clues which lead us to believe that they had a great deal of contact with the Dofus. We still don\'t know what the connection was, there is much left to uncover.";
D.q[4207] = "We love to send groups of adventurers to certain defeat. Otomai and I often bet on how long the adventurers have to live. That\'s why we don\'t let just anyone confront the Kimbo, we hate making useless bets. Therefore, I\'ll only let you confront him if you can show me that you\'re worth the fight. Go and take on the Tynril. If you can defeat such a creature you might stay alive with the Kimbo for a few minutes, and Muleze will certainly give you the key to get into the Kimbo Canopy.";
D.q[5359] = "";
D.q[5093] = "";
D.q[8110] = "";
D.q[7228] = "";
D.q[5872] = "";
D.q[6907] = "I told you already, I\'m just an apprentice. I can\'t help you, sorry.";
D.q[2209] = "Have a look mate! A pure link to nature, as master SadadI\'d say. And I think that will come in handy: nature sensed something evil in the tunnels, and Enutrofs are in danger! If you have some time before your nap, can you go there and see what\'s going on? I must help the master, he\'s having a hard time.";
D.q[4204] = "I only let the most courageous adventurers venture in this old lab. Prove your worth and go help my friend, Captain Futchure defeat his sworn enemy, Gourlo the Terrible. I lost a whole supply of Greedo Rum over him and I\'ll never forgive that. Most importantly, bring me the Bherb Gully Key if you wish to gain entry.";
D.q[2208] = "Hm! Sick and tired of me, are you? Here you go, I\'ve some \'urrywood left but be careful, iss verry verry rare sing!";
D.q[4212] = "Ahem, according to your constitution, I can tell that I\'ll need a Great Coralator relic, a Gourlo the Terrible relic, a Greater Bherb relic and a Tynril relic to prepare your potion. Once ground to powder, I\'ll be able to withdraw all the magic power I need from them.";
D.q[4752] = "Why would I shut myself away with an old Bontarian toad when there are so many wonderful Cras around here?\nTake this, it\'s a message detailing exactly what I think of his suggestion.";
D.q[7225] = "";
D.q[1154] = "We keep your pet for a fee.\nYou entrust me with your pet and money, I\'ll guarantee his safe keeping with a contract.\nWhen you come back, show me the certificate plus a little more money and you\'ll get your pet back.\nSimple.";
D.q[6267] = "Here\'s the Crystal. Now let my niece go.";
D.q[4213] = "Ahem, according to your constitution, I can tell that I\'ll need a Great Coralator relic, a Gourlo the Terrible relic, a Greater Bherb relic, a Tynril relic and a Kimbo relic to prepare your potion. Once ground to powder, I\'ll be able to withdraw all the magic power I need from them.";
D.q[4088] = "Ahem, according to your constitution, I can tell that I\'ll need a Great Coralator relic, a Gourlo the Terrible relic, a Greater Bherb relic, a Tynril relic and a Kimbo relic to prepare your potion. Once ground to powder, I\'ll be able to withdraw all the magic power I need from them.";
D.q[582] = "Oh, that\'s very nice of you, thank you! If you bring me all the items I need to build a raft, I\'ll give you a pet!";
D.q[4086] = "Ahem, according to your constitution, I can tell that I\'ll need a Great Coralator relic, a Gourlo the Terrible relic and a Greater Bherb relic to prepare your potion. Once ground to powder, I\'ll be able to withdraw all the magic power I need from them.";
D.q[6908] = "I am not an expert in carving such precise patterns. I specialise in weapons, not ornamentation. You should contact Oli Venders instead, he will be glad to help, I\'m sure.";
D.q[2265] = "Shoot! I\'ve just ruined my scissors... again! I need a new pair, but I can\'t leave my shop empty...\nCould you go get me scissors at the forge market? I\'d be very grateful... Go and find a guy called Two-fingers, he\'s sooo good at that stuff...";
D.q[4085] = "Ahem, according to your constitution, I can tell that I\'ll need a Great Coralator relic and a Gourlo the Terrible relic to prepare your potion. Once ground to powder, I\'ll be able to withdraw all the magic power I need from them.";
D.q[4210] = "Ahem, according to your constitution, I can tell that I\'ll need a Great Coralator relic and a Gourlo the Terrible relic to prepare your potion. Once ground to powder, I\'ll be able to withdraw all the magic power I need from them.";
D.q[4619] = "And you wish to learn how to use it? Join me in the basement of the Alchemists\' Market and we\'ll carry out the Revelation Ritual. In a corner is a cupboard. Stand in front of this cupboard and follow the passage that will open up before you. You\'ll need to bring two trusted friends with you, I want to help but I don\'t want to do your work for you. I\'ll make a list of the items you\'ll need. Bring them with you and everything should go well, unless you replace the Magical Cure for a Sulphur Pouch. It\'s very important you don\'t have any sulphur in your inventory, understood?";
D.q[6662] = "If you think you\'ve made a mistake with your alignment, my colleague Morgan Faym\'n, in charge of the AnKama Castle Militia, will be able to help you become neutral, for a fee. If that\'s what you want, I can show you where she\'s.";
D.q[5246] = "";
D.q[5127] = "";
D.q[944] = "Hi, I\'m Barry Flaye, the Hotbread\'s best customer. I strongly recommend their beer. It\'s the best in Bonta... no question!";
D.q[2371] = "Oh, you need to ask Ahenn for these kinds of things, she\'s on the first floor of the professions building. Do you want me to tell you where it\'s?";
D.q[5245] = "";
D.q[4195] = "A good captain should never leave his ship and I hope that one day I\'ll be able to return my girl to the sea! I\'m doing my best to hold off the pirates but their greater numbers have always prevented me from gaining the upper hand. To do this, we would first need to defeat their captain, known as Gourlo the Terrible. But I don\'t let just anyone confront him. You must prove yourself worthy of it. That\'s why I ask all adventurers who wish to confront Gourlo to show me the key to get into the ark.";
D.q[7229] = "";
D.q[3136] = "But don\'t worry, in exchange, I\'ll give you the key to get into Skeunk\'s hideout. I used to guard the entrance of the hideout before being exiled here for attempted rebellion. Haha... I can see that you\'re wondering why you should go to Skeunk\'s hideout. Well, it\'s simple. Skeunk himself stole the Koolich\'s Dofus - see what I mean...\n\nSo, where\'s this Koolich set?";
D.q[1568] = "How will I provide for my wife and kids if you put me out of business? Have mercy!";
D.q[4232] = "Don\'t be afraid, the bacteria you see is in reality microscopic. The magnifying effect of the ice can play tricks. Its power is another matter, however. don\'t even think about taking it on... It\'s... unusual.";
D.q[7458] = "";
D.q[5443] = "";
D.q[4205] = "Defeating Silf the Greater Bherb the way you did was just a brilliant performance, as brilliant as a firebaby\'s kneecap.";
D.q[3985] = "Be quiet you ignowant wascal! The monstew is coming, don\'t you heaw it? It\'s too late now... It will leap at ouw thwoat... Be weady, you\'ll be my squiwe since you awe hewe! Let\'s unsheathe our swowds and kill this monstew.";
D.q[462] = "Howdy sailor! Have you finished what you were supposed to do?\nIf you have, let\'s get outta here!";
D.q[6212] = "How would I know who X is. I\'ve no interest in people ever since he left.";
D.q[4200] = "However, I must warn you. The Tynril is an original creature which surprises many the fool. I only let the most courageous adventurers enter this old lab. To show me your value, you\'ll have to confront Silf the Greater Bherb. He\'s a terrifying enemy but if you defeat him Rubrat will give you a key to enter the lab.";
D.q[5131] = "";
D.q[1050] = "Huh, what debt are you talking about? There must be some mistake.";
D.q[1169] = "Huh... Come back later... a fish is calling me...";
D.q[2626] = "However... you seem to be quite in love with him and that matters a lot to me. If you only knew how much I love my son! You can have him for 50,000!";
D.q[2636] = "Huh... What? You... You know my daughter?\nAnd you\'re.... hum... well, anything can happen here in Pandala, so...\nWhat the heck.... Just go see her and she can decide!";
D.q[7230] = "";
D.q[6909] = "Mmm... Show me the diagram.\nYes, I can carve this bark, but it will cost you 500 Kamas. What do you say?";
D.q[1496] = "Huh? What do you want me to... Hem, wait a minute... you\'ve been promoted recently. You have to display your new rank. Go and buy yourself the basic Brakmarian equipment. Here is a little bit of money, compliments of the tax payer, heheh! Take this list of basic equipment, buy it all and show me what you look like.";
D.q[2828] = "Be quiet! I\'m not stupid! You don\'t give me any choice. Tomorrow you\'ll disappear forever. We\'ll throw you into a tank of pure Pandka... You know too much. Sometimes you have to make a few sacrifices before you get what you want.";
D.q[2481] = "Thanks a lot! I can fix the bamboo now! Come to think of it, I don\'t think a bug could have done this. The bamboo looks like it has been burnt by some sort of acid... I\'ve never seen such a thing!";
D.q[5045] = "Hello, welcome to the village of Amakna. The old village was destroyed by Dreggons, so the inhabitants of Amakna took refuge here. As you may have noticed, the village is ecstatic.\nAll the same, my men and guards are here to make sure nobody spoils the fun.";
D.q[7231] = "";
D.q[3731] = "Hello kid! What can I get for you?";
D.q[1529] = "Hum, I don\'t remember your face, are you new round here?\nCan you tell me how you heard about this place?";
D.q[6052] = "";
D.q[2249] = "Hum, OK... In that case, the next Gobball I\'ll kill will be hers.";
D.q[1306] = "Hi my friend #1! What can I do for you?";
D.q[4815] = "You\'re back! It\'s been a while. What do you want to know?";
D.q[925] = "Hello sweetheart! Welcome to Bagrutte\'s Inn!";
D.q[1647] = "Hello! Welcome to Maxims! The best restaurant in the whole fair - if not the whole land. What do you want? Some fast food cooked with care and patience? A slow boiling stew on the double? You\'ve come to the right place, I\'ve what you need! Just ask!";
D.q[2686] = "You\'re coming nowhere... or I\'ll smack you in the face!";
D.q[6910] = "Let\'s see, it doesn\'t look too difficult...\nA nick here, a rasp there...\nThis bit needs polishing...\nAnd there\'s the result!\nNo need to thank me, I was just doing my job. However, if I were you I would avoid setting foot in the Amakna Cemetery. It seems that the dead attack the living there.";
D.q[1100] = "Hum, no, it\'s a complicated recipe, not to mention a well-guarded secret. So it\'s hidden in my house on a big piece of paper! Ha-ha!";
D.q[578] = "Hum, sorry but it\'s not enough... I\'m missing something. I need 4 masks and... an extra colour! Bring me the masks and a paint kit otherwise I won\'t be able to make a lifelike mask. Where can you find paint? teehee...How would I know?! Heehee..";
D.q[4216] = "Be careful, when you drink this potion you\'ll only get back the characteristic points that you invested after you reached 101.\nWith this potion, you won\'t to lose the characteristic points that you earned with scrolls.\nBut you won\'t be able to get back the characteristic points that you invested under your 101 characteristic points. \nAre you sure you want to continue? ";
D.q[5044] = "";
D.q[2513] = "Hum, well a fake Dofus... but it\'s been sculpted into precious ore by a handy little Enutrofette... Trust me!";
D.q[1391] = "Be careful, you\'re approaching the war front. Nothing to report here.";
D.q[5138] = "";
D.q[5204] = "";
D.q[1326] = "Are you sure? This kind of secret will only become a burden. An ancient time demon is not much appreciated among the idiots of today. Could it change your destiny?";
D.q[7232] = "";
D.q[7107] = "";
D.q[1508] = "Humm, apparently it\'s not yet the best place to attack...";
D.q[5637] = "You know the best part? I found out that someone had his identity stolen by a friend of his, and he never knew a thing. Can you imagine? Your friend robbing you, it\'s crazy. You know what, now that I think of it, it\'s probably a little too crazy to be true. How could you steal someone\'s identity, especially from a friend of yours! You have your identity, I\'ve mine, we can\'t just switch between the two! It\'s really, really crazy.";
D.q[6911] = "If it\'s for carving some wood, it\'s different. I am willing to give use my time and skills to help but it will cost you 500 Kamas.";
D.q[2534] = "Here are the three commandments of the goddess: Drink, Guzzle and Fight. Here is a piece of advice: go visit the wise Lenald. He\'s the only one on this island who will tell you the truth! Take this amulet with you and he\'ll know that you\'re coming as a friend!";
D.q[1888] = "Hello, how can I help you?";
D.q[4013] = "Humpf! If I got a job, at least I\'d earn a few honest Kamas!";
D.q[2195] = "Hurry up and bring me everything I need before the Ecaflips come to challenge me again!";
D.q[1032] = "Hello, my grocery store is open 24 hours a day. If you\'re looking for something to eat, please have a look at our stock.";
D.q[5123] = "Humph, I\'ve been putting on so much weight lately... that won\'t do my tightrope act any good!";
D.q[2701] = "Because Grandapan has one foot on Pandala and the other in the kingdom of the gods! I\'m here and yet I\'m nowhere to be found. I can hear the heartbeat of each and every Dofus! The goddess told Grandapan that when the Dofus are all united, the chosen one will be blessed by the gods!";
D.q[6912] = "Thanks, now, please leave me alone and above all, don\'t interrupt me.\n...\n...\nWell, I hope you like the result.\nIf you really want to set foot in the Amakna Cemetery, I\'d advise extreme caution. It seems that its crypts are infested with haemophiliac bloodsuckers, and their thirst is insatiable.";
D.q[2051] = "Hurry up and go to the blacksmith\'s . He\'ll melt those Kamas to make you a mighty blade - as mighty as your arm - out of it.";
D.q[7451] = "";
D.q[4302] = "Are you sure you want to go back to the lab? \nAs you wish ... but you won\'t be able to get in unless you bring me a piece of polished brain. You\'ll find them on the Polished Cracklers that wander the plains.";
D.q[5103] = "Hurry up, and if anyone tries to stop you, kill them.";
D.q[2293] = "Huuum? Leave me alone please, I\'m thinking......";
D.q[6602] = "I admire your skill, I understand why Amayiro thinks so much of you. Go back to him while we wait for the enchantment to take effect. Come back and see me when the doll is ready. Now that I think of it, take this purse of Kamas, everyone who is willing to serve the attendant is rewarded generously. If you continue to serve me well, you have every chance of climbing through the ranks of the militia, don\'t forget that. The Goddess Jiva appreciates men who are dedicated heart and body to the cause.";
D.q[7531] = "Which Doploons do you want to exchange?";
D.q[3457] = "Where do you want to go?";
D.q[2703] = "I know vely little my fliend. But I know enough to please you. Bling a flask of Pandapiler to my old fwiend, the Chief of the village of Akwadala. And I\'ll tell you evelything I know about the Dofus of Pandala.";
D.q[7525] = "Which Doploons do you want to exchange?";
D.q[5674] = "You\'re like a little weed... hard to tear up and always coming back. By the time I\'m finished with you, even your mother won\'t recognise you.";
D.q[7528] = "Which Doploons do you want to exchange?";
D.q[1729] = "Cras can use any weapon, but they handle bows and daggers best.";
D.q[7529] = "Which Doploons do you want to exchange?";
D.q[7530] = "Which Doploons do you want to exchange?";
D.q[4083] = "Which spell do you want to unlearn?";
D.q[3048] = "Welcome #1.\nI\'m surprised to see you here. You\'re very lucky that a Crocodyl didn\'t devour you on your way...\nThis sanctuary is infested with terrible pet ghosts, ghosts of those pets abandoned by adventurers. They only obey their master Oshima, Oshimo\'s father, who owns the Bow Kennel near Sufokia.";
D.q[6093] = "I always recognise my mistakes, and you haven\'t heard the last from me about convincing Maimane to join Brakmar\'s side.";
D.q[3766] = "Welcome, #1. It\'s a blessing indeed to be incarnated at the foot of your god\'s statue. If adventure is in your blood, Incarnam is a good place to start shedding some. Later, young one, you may descend to the continent.";
D.q[7424] = "";
D.q[6054] = "I am Silvosse, the pruning master and Protector of the month of Flovor. I might as well tell you now - I don\'t like being disturbed for no reason.";
D.q[5280] = "";
D.q[5113] = "I am Zo, but most people call me Sacri Zo. I was given a position of high responsibility not so long ago, but people say I\'m even worse than the guy I replaced.";
D.q[4331] = "Just hop on in this wonderful cannon! Don\'t worry, there\'s an oxygen mask in there if things go wrong.";
D.q[472] = "Mowning to you, little-cawwotted man. I\'ve a gweat deal to offew you. If you bwing me back 100 Cawwots fwom Cawote\'s, I\'ll giwe you a spell of my own cweation. My bwothews awe afwaid of me and my stwange ideas, they hawe locked me hewe with no food... If you can steal something to eat fow them, my spell is youws.";
D.q[1230] = "Welcome to the Burnt Cat Inn. Are you here to celebrate the death of the owner?";
D.q[1124] = "You\'re looking for a knuckle sandwich? Lucky you found me then! Hehehe!";
D.q[1556] = "I\'m concerned about my Tabi, it was bitten by a Scurvion while I was travelling in the Sidimote Lands. It looks a bit unwell now...";
D.q[4055] = "Hello adventurer. As you can see, I\'m Ghard, the famous Mounded Ghard! \nI\'m in charge of King Allister\'s mounts. He entrusted me with a mission for which I must find a new mount for each of his men. \nWould you like to help me?";
D.q[2029] = "I\'m not wrong, am I!? But before even thinking about glory, you\'ll need a weapon, a good sword. I\'ve a very good friend called Two-Fingers, he\'s a smith. He\'ll help you make one and then I can affix our mark on it. I\'ve shown you the way. Just follow your compass now. Good luck!";
D.q[171] = "Welcome to the Inn, what thirst quenching, foaming beverage can I get for you, adventurer?";
D.q[2786] = "I\'m not a Bwak. I just fell into one of those damned springs trying to escape those morons!";
D.q[6913] = "What? You came here as...as...as a tourist? How dare you mock me like that!\nFor the trouble I\'ll give you a hiding instead!";
D.q[2319] = "There are loads of sick Tofus in these underground galleries. Eniripsas asked us to get a few feathers for medical tests, but it\'s a pain in the neck to catch the animals... I\'d need a good deal of feathers : besides the fact that Eniripsas want to get some, it\'s a really good business! 10 feathers of these sick Tofus should be enough.";
D.q[6274] = "Work for the head of the Brakmar militia? I hadn\'t considered it. What have I to gain out of it?";
D.q[3665] = "This damned Zaap never works. I\'ve hit it with hundreds of different hammers! I hope Xelor comes to fix it soon. By the Twelve, I\'m tired. I can\'t even go to the toilet until my shift\'s up.";
D.q[674] = "Who told you I\'ve a secret? You\'re spying on me, aren\'t you? You want to know the secret of the Chaferfu Summoning, is that right?";
D.q[5502] = "";
D.q[4136] = "I\'m the Black and Pink Knight.\nNo one can cross this bridge without confronting me first.";
D.q[6915] = "Have you lost your mind? Actually, I don\'t care if you want to sacrifice yourself willingly, it suits me down to the ground. So, no regrets?";
D.q[2114] = "You\'re not an Ecaflip, are you?";
D.q[652] = "We\'ve a recipe even an Enutrof would never use, so I\'ll give it to you:\nForgetfulness of Luck: 3 old Four-Leaf Clovers, 70 Five-Leaf Clovers, 30 Krokette Amulets\nAmusing, isn\'t it? I\'d say! What what?";
D.q[692] = "I\'m so disappointed,,,  You\'ve just signed your own death warrant.";
D.q[4558] = "Ah yes, that rumour. Hmm, bring me some empty turtle shells from Moon to decorate my Tavern, and I\'ll tell you about it. One of each colour, please.";
D.q[6916] = "So, you\'re looking for the Hammer of Light. You will never find where I hid it, and as I am very thirsty, you must now die.";
D.q[2775] = "So, you need a Shamanic certificate to practise Pandawushuka?\n*The Shaman comes near you. He puts his fatty fingers on your eyelids and stares deep into your eyes*\n\nThe Brücknawa test is definitive, if the back of the eye is perfect and has no trouble refracting, I\'ve no objection to the practice of Pandawushuka.";
D.q[2827] = "Us Pandikazes, represent the genuine paragon of the Pandawas! This Grandipan is an idiot... Opening the island to strangers, sharing our legends with them, advertising for the bloody Dofus hunt.... Don\'t you get it? The Dofus only bring devastation and misery?!\nYou must get it right, it\'s not about the Dofus themselves but about unscrupulous adventurers like YOU! Chaos is all you bring... We can\'t stand it anymore!";
D.q[6261] = "I ate him. Hehehe.";
D.q[6917] = "If I tell you give you give me my underpants back?\nHere\'s the hammer, but without its powers. I had fifteen years to try to chase away the Spirit of Light who lived inside it. I fought each day and night without respite, and my efforts finally paid off. So you get the hammer because you beat me, but it\'s useless to you. Hahaha!";
D.q[325] = "We are a secret clan composed of the vilest, cruellest and most feared beings in all Amakna province. We are sometimes employed as mercenaries by key figures who don\'t want to be involved in dubious business...";
D.q[2] = "I\'m one of #1\'s perceptors.\nThe guild hasn\'t been doing too well recently.\nI\'ll make an exception this time and not join in the fights.";
D.q[4130] = "I think we\'ve beached on the wrong island... According to my map, we\'re on Castaways\' Island, which is more than a little strange. I don\'t understand how it happened. I might have had some digestive problems and got the directions wrong. I thought the Kaniger ears you brought me for breakfast tasted a little off. Well, you\'d better find us a way out of here while I give the orders and supervise the repairs to the ship.";
D.q[3678] = "I believe in the moment. If there\'s no moment, well then, what is there? You must get to the moment is what I\'m trying to say. But the moment is now... what? Hey, look, for the moment just go find some wool. I\'ll get back to you on that one. Understand?";
D.q[4172] = "To which Scaraport do you want to go?";
D.q[6918] = "That\'s very annoying, we\'ll have to find a solution. The Vampire said he had driven away the spirit, no? He didn\'t say he had destroyed it, so that\'s a good thing. I will not forget to mention your help to Amayiro.\nNow, back to your work, I\'ll tell you as soon as I\'ve decided what to do about the hammer.";
D.q[1941] = "Wisdom has guided you here my friend. I\'ll teach how to treat the worst pains and wounds that ever existed. Even the worst of all: the Cephal Algia. But first of all, you need the right tools that is, a wand. Can we start?";
D.q[2825] = "A secret meeting is being held in Aerdala at the moment. We don\'t know anything about what\'s going on over there... But we do know one thing - it\'s about the Dofus. The wise Lenald wants to send you over there, as it\'s difficult to trust anyone at the moment... Pandikazes are everywhere. Master Lenald is sure you\'re not one of them. But be careful: there have been mysterious disappearances of Pandawas over there. Pandikazes are said to be responsible for the said disappearances and to have the inhabitants of Aerdala as allies. You must infiltrate their clan and bring back as much information as you can to us. Go see the wise one if you come back alive.";
D.q[673] = "Do you want another magical tool?\nAlright, I can sell you one at a reasonable price. 2,000 Kamas and it\'s yours!";
D.q[2750] = "You want to have a stroll through the Damned Forest? You need to pass a little test before you do. Defeat this Dopple to prove you\'re able for these crazy woods. But just go there for a walk, huh? Don\'t even think of challenging Dark Vlad!";
D.q[3446] = "I believe you. Use my recipe but please bring it back to me once you\'re done with it.";
D.q[657] = "You want to get married? It will certainly fill the heart of the Gods of Amakna with joy. To be linked by the sacred and INDESTRUCTIBLE bonds of marriage, you\'ll both have to appear dressed for the occasion and in possession of the wedding rings. I\'ll celebrate your union after the exchange of the rings, you\'ll BE FOREVER LINKED. Such is the will of our Gods.";
D.q[4162] = "I bet it\'s my husband that sent you! He\'s good-for-nothing, a nice guy, but still good-for-nothing! He cares more for his creatures and his research than for me. The romance is gone... and we don\'t share the things that a couple is supposed to share anymore.\nBut I do know that he loves me, I can hear his heart beat fast from here.... he just doesn\'t know how to communicate and share his passion with simple gestures or even words or looks.";
D.q[3130] = "I already feel a lot better. You\'ve just saved my life and I intend to thank you for it by sharing my knowledge on Dragoturkeys with you. I\'m the best Dragoturkey Breeder you\'ll find on the continent... my books are available in every serious library around, and respected by anyone who\'s anyone in the world of Dragoturkeys!";
D.q[1161] = "I buy you young wild boar, buddy! 5,000 Kama! Good price!!! Last price...";
D.q[1143] = "Here is the letter. Hurry, it\'s very urgent.";
D.q[2881] = "Capturing a group of souls is real easy. First, you must keep an empty soul stone in your hand while fighting.\nThen, you must cast a spell at the end of the fight in order to send the souls flying into the air... finally you must try to catch them.\n\nBe careful! If the spell is cast too soon, it\'ll vanish and you won\'t be able to catch any wandering souls.\n\nAbout this spell, well... I can\'t teach it to you. But it seems it can be found in deep caves on Pandala Island.";
D.q[7425] = "";
D.q[6307] = "You\'re so ugly that even the powers of 1,000 gods could not fulfil your request.";
D.q[6573] = "I can finally start building my traps to stop intruders wandering about here. \nNo, my traps can\'t tell the difference between visitors and intruders... so what?";
D.q[3350] = "I can give you a key and teleport you directly to the entrance of the dungeon you want to go to.\nSo, to which dungeon do you wish to go?";
D.q[2547] = "I can picture your face if the Pandikazes found out it was YOU who brought the Dofus to Grandapan!";
D.q[1500] = "I can make the most powerful weapons. Nothing is immune to their ferocity. But everything has a price, heheh...";
D.q[663] = "I can give you some Great Scrolls of Wisdom if you can bring me back 90 Mushrooms, 75 Sunflower Seeds, 60 Hemp Seeds and 200 Moskito Wings.";
D.q[5904] = "You\'re still bugging me. Tell me what\'s brought you here, quick.";
D.q[3813] = "I can see in the way you walk you\'re gonna be a success. Listen up. If you defeat my pet\'s father... well, it\'s not his biological father, but he raised the... look, if you defeat the big, angry creature over there, I\'ll stick this key to the Snoowolf Dungeon in your pocket. How about that?";
D.q[1413] = "Aaare yoouu puuulliing my leeeg! Yoouu reeaally waant threee innooceent peeopleee tooo dieeeee? Ooooh I seeee, yoouu\'re juust liiike theese yooouuung braainnleesss deemoonnss. Geet looost aand neeveer cooomee baackk heeeerrrre aaggaiin. I haaatee deemooons liikee yoouu, iiif I seee yoouu aggaiin yoouu wwill paay foor tthhaatt aaffffrrontt!";
D.q[2931] = "I see you know about the existence of elemental tonics that only great Pandawushu masters can make! \nAs the Water Pandawushu master, I can clear away the wave of danger which is continually threatening you and I can bring you a protective effervescence for you next fights...";
D.q[2793] = "I can see in your eyes that you\'re attracted by the secret treasures of the Damned Forest.";
D.q[2635] = "HHEEIIITIITT!\n*Breathes deeply*\nIt must be a mistake. I can\'t break the engagement or my poor daughter will have no one to marry, do you understand?";
D.q[3403] = "Mission completed. Bzztt... Your new mi... bztt kriiiik! Frtrtttt";
D.q[6563] = "Wow, it\'s amazing. You guarantee it\'s never been used? I don\'t want to catch anything!\nI\'m finally going to be able to get rid of the old one. No more red raw skin and scabs!\nI\'ve to test it again just to make sure you aren\'t doing one over on me.";
D.q[3027] = "Hello my friend! Do you like living in the open-air? Are you looking for a healthy activity that will bring you la joie de vivre? Are you sick of being surrounded by Mush Mush and Larvae? Lucky you found me! I\'ve what you need!";
D.q[5883] = "";
D.q[3028] = "How to become a perfect Brakmarian inductee! With this manual in your pocket, you\'re promised to a brilliant career in our beautiful city Militia! Take it! Everything\'s explained inside! Enjoy the reading! If you make up your mind to join our ranks, go and see Oto Mustam! he\'s next to the Militia in the city of Brakmar!";
D.q[3043] = "We always need the good offices of a priest!\nResurrecting foolish adventurers is what I do best. You\'ll be able to do it too, if you persist in the Order that of Bonta or Brakmar...\nBefore reaching this advanced stage, please note that to get your energy back, nothing\'s better than a nice potion made by an alchemist! But you know, these drinks called Raid: the Pahoa, the Ghetto and the last one Raid Boole don\'t taste very good, but they really pep you up!";
D.q[4407] = "Xarthan is undoubtedly innocent, but we have to be sure. Go back to Brakmar and question our mole. I\'ve a feeling that the Brakmarians have something to do with our problems. While you\'re gone I\'m going to have a chat with Xarthan and Ture Inge - it\'s always good to get the opinion of an expert.";
D.q[274] = "You\'re talking nonsense! \nThat\'s something every Eniripsa should know.";
D.q[1234] = "Brakmarians are not much liked around these parts. You\'d better clear off...";
D.q[378] = "Yeah maaan! Far out, maaaaan! Peace, maaaan! Slide along the wheat! It\'s the Bob Man! Since our Guru, Skippy, gave me the recipe for these Mushroom and Sunflower Seed doughnuts, I\'m totally in agreement with the gods. It\'s great, man! But I need a few thing to make some more.\nBring me 80 Mushrooms and 60 Sunflower seeds and I\'ll reward you with a Wisdom Scroll.";
D.q[2473] = "I\'ve lost it all.... don\'t even have two Kamas to rub together....";
D.q[5881] = "";
D.q[1091] = "Pfff, I\'m knackered.";
D.q[5882] = "";
D.q[1205] = "Did Justfa send you?\nI\'ve neither the strength nor the courage to go with you.\nTake this badge, Justfa will use it to ratify your joining.";
D.q[3144] = "You\'re lucky to have made it this far. If the elements hadn\'t created a breach through this mountain, I\'d never have had to suffer your miserable presence.\nYou\'re already getting on my nerves and I know you want to steal my Dofus, so just take it and get out of here! But before, give me back my key and my disciples\' brooches! I don\'t want to give you another occasion to come here and be obliged to humiliate you for good.";
D.q[3667] = "I can\'t reveal the divine secrets of Xelor to just anyone, you know, but it\'s no secret that Xelors are always late! That\'s why their god created Zaaps, and smaller portals, Zaapis - it lets them get where they need to go without breaking a sweat. If you want to use a Zaapi, it\'ll cost you two Kamas.";
D.q[5970] = "I can\'t see your pet. What does it look like?";
D.q[3148] = "Finally! An apology! It was about time!\nBut this is not enough, I\'ll have to build a new boomerang and I order you to bring me back everything I need to make it!\nIf you bring me back 10 Brown Warko Boomerangs, 10 Bloody Koalak Boomerangs, 10 Dok Alako Boomerangs and 10 Master Koalak Boomerangs, I\'ll be able to make myself a new boomerang.\nIf you manage to bring all this back to me, I\'ll reward you and most importantly, I\'ll pray Skeunk and ask him to spare your life next time he meets you!";
D.q[7233] = "";
D.q[3385] = "Ver\' good! Here! Take this key for the next job. Get goin\'!";
D.q[3219] = "I\'d not advise you to venture alone in this maze. Be careful though, the doors of each room close after you\'ve gone through thus making it very difficult to progress as a team if you\'re going through the same rooms at the same time! I\'d advise you to use your map to progress in this maze or else you\'ll quickly get lost. Indeed, some adventurers say that if you keep on going in the same direction, you end up back to the point where you started. Funny, isn\'t it? Don\'t forget that this maze is quite complex but logical. If you want to progress in a direction, doors will close behind and in front of you. You\'ll have to constantly change directions. If you end up trapped, don\'t hesitate to ask other adventurers for help. They can open the doors of the room you\'re in if they get close enough in the right direction. See... easy as pie!";
D.q[7234] = "";
D.q[714] = "I can\'t talk to you today... But you could perhaps make yourself useful... Can you bring me 20 Wholemeal Breads? My guys are ravenous. We\'re not too far from the baking district, you\'ll surely find some over there...";
D.q[3247] = "Deprived of light and food, Dragons, Dreggons and Dragoss that were locked up in the sanctuary started to hibernate some hundreds of years ago. But god Osamodas never forgot this affront... His own disciples had betrayed him. Out of revenge, he woke up the creatures trapped in this sanctuary and it didn\'t take them long before they could escape and destroy the village and its inhabitants.";
D.q[1488] = "I can\'t teach you the slightest thing about fishing because you\'re still training for another activity. Come back when you\'ve made some progress in the other trade.";
D.q[4691] = "I can\'t wait to hold that blade in my hands. Go find the Corruptite.";
D.q[2706] = "I can see by youl bloodshot eye that you finished youl mission! You deselve to know the stoly of oul people... which is somehow linked to the stoly of the Dofus!";
D.q[2977] = "Yep, it\'d be better. I\'d not recommend going to Pandala before visiting our beautiful city. Here, you\'ll learn everything you need to know to be a living adventurer... Read the manual I\'ve just added to your inventory as soon as you can. To consult it, all you need to do is to lay your hands on it, then it\'s just like using any other items. Goodbye and good riddance!";
D.q[7235] = "";
D.q[5141] = "";
D.q[5500] = "";
D.q[1459] = "Heheheh, you were ridiculous...a complete loser. Clear off, I\'m in a good mood so I\'ll spare your life.";
D.q[7236] = "";
D.q[980] = "Wanted poster?";
D.q[4137] = "You\'re worthy to cross the bridge.";
D.q[3336] = "When you\'re stronger, you\'ll be able to locate resources in the Koalak region.";
D.q[3367] = "How charming and haughty! Well, as you wish. Go talk to the Key Master. Should you carry out all the missions he\'ll give you, then, I\'ll personally place the family relic in your hands. There is no artefact as powerful in the World of Twelve.";
D.q[6616] = "";
D.q[7237] = "";
D.q[5342] = "Ronan: Bwork. Beurk. Bwowowo. Bwork.";
D.q[3398] = "Your new mission, should you choose to accept it, will be to infiltrate the dungeon that this key opens. Once inside, you\'ll have to be sure the local creatures don\'t notice you. You\'ll have to go to the very bottom of the dungeon. If you or any member of your group is to be captured, I\'ll deny any knowledge of your actions. Good luck. End of communication.";
D.q[7238] = "";
D.q[1937] = "Hey there #1! You come down to lend our little company a hand? We sure could use some help. You gotta be a brave one, but there\'s gold in them thar hills! So you in?... yeah! A\'right, well, you got insurance, kid... we all got insurance, don\'t we boys... ha, ha! Take a look at that face! You\'re one dumb critter... \nA\'right I want one thing done first... bring this here letter down to Howard Yeahbutno, he\'s a Iop and a good friend o\' mine. You got that kid? Just follow your compass, you can\'t miss him!";
D.q[2561] = "A long time ago, the Lenalds wele the plotectols of a Dofus. Envied by the Pandawas of Feudala, they plotted with those vile Wabbits! And we, the Lenalds, wele kicked off oul own island... But tluth is elsewhele... Go to Wabbit\'sland, and you\'ll find out!";
D.q[3415] = "Ah, perfect timing, I\'m looking for people to help me confront the gods. They took the liberty of reducing the power of my Sacrifices, and for no reason at all! It\'s a disgrace! They didn\'t even ask my opinion first!  \nWell, anyway, I think I\'ll confront them another day. I\'ve better things to do right now. \nWhat do you want, by the way?";
D.q[3224] = "I could tell you what I know about the Porco Rusto people and the Dragon Pig, I like informing silly little tourists like you. Let\'s start with a story, a true story...\nGoultard was the name of the legendary sword of the famous Ecaflip, Garathgoul. Garathgoul went in search of the Dragon Pig, because he knew that the Dragon Pig concealed the famous Turquoise Dofus in his den. He found the Dragon Pig and fought it with his magic and his sword! Garathgoul fought hard to save his skin and his sword Goultard was soaked in the stinking blood of the Dragon Pig. Then, a spark fell when the Ecaflip cast his favourite spell. The spark fell into a puddle of mud, and they say it gave life to the people of Porcos Rustos. There, I\'ve told you everything I know about this legend.";
D.q[2501] = "Hola! You have a sharp eye, that\'s a sign of intelligence! I think we\'ll get on just fine you and me... You\'re coming to pay your McSheth levy? Buy this wonderful hand-made Pandawan headgear from me and you\'ll be all square!";
D.q[5051] = "";
D.q[7239] = "";
D.q[5668] = "I didn\'t expect you to succeed so easily, but there\'s no harm in that. Your reward for capturing one is to join the ranks of the Soul Hunters.";
D.q[6617] = "";
D.q[3490] = "Good idea! Nevertheless, I have to defend my honour as a Bwork veteran. I must retaliate.";
D.q[3517] = "Thank you so much! As soon as I find how to give it life, I\'ll be the happiest Bwork ever bworn. I hope all this meat will not rot till then!";
D.q[5210] = "Have you got Raaga\'s notes?";
D.q[5331] = "";
D.q[5336] = "";
D.q[3046] = "I didn\'t lie to you, did I? This is the most beautiful castle of all!";
D.q[686] = "Answer these 3 questions\nOnly by assertions.\nThe first is the easiest,\nHow many thousands to spend for a lover ?";
D.q[6762] = "Victory! Thank you for your help. We may not have won if not for you.";
D.q[3676] = "You again. My, my, you\'re mysterious. Aren\'t you done with your quest yet? If at first you don\'t succeed... you know the rest!";
D.q[5339] = "";
D.q[7240] = "";
D.q[3687] = "I didn\'t notice anything wrong. All clear.";
D.q[1530] = "Hi there, if you\'re looking for beer bread or bread beer, you\'ve come to the right place!";
D.q[3753] = "I haven\'t made too many Kamas round these parts. I got plenty of items to trade though. You interested stranger?";
D.q[3404] = "Scannnnn.... unknown code...";
D.q[1277] = "I\'ve been told there is a weak point in the Brakmar ramparts, North-West of the cemetery. I\'d like you to find this entrance and evaluate the risks.\nBe careful of the Brakmar Chafer Archers. Their chief can kill a man with a single arrow. I don\'t have to tell you that going alone would be suicide...";
D.q[1567] = "Very well, ha-ha! Come and bet on a Tofu fight some time...\nAnd take this brooch as a sign of our friendship.";
D.q[726] = "I don\'t have anything left for you to do. But ask the guards at the entrance, I\'ve heard they need a hand.";
D.q[4097] = "I don\'t have the time. I\'ve so many things to take care of!";
D.q[3396] = "I don\'t have anything left. Get out! Shoo! Off with you!";
D.q[5145] = "";
D.q[7128] = "";
D.q[818] = "A squirrel stole the key to the Brakmar Prism room. Don\'t ask me why or how the little rascal did it, but several soldiers saw it happen. \nIf we don\'t get it back, you may well end up on the gallows. Know what I mean?\nI already have guards keeping watch over the bridge, the squirrel can\'t escape!";
D.q[3845] = "How beauuuutiful!!! I\'m-a sooo taaalented! I\'m-a da grreatest arrtist everrr! My muuuse, inspiiire me!";
D.q[2047] = "Well, she bet that the Enutrofs weren\'t courageous enough to dare to go into the underground passages \"with all those creatures wandering around blahblahbli blahblahblah\". \"On the contrary!\", I told her, \"They\'ll rush in there to find their fortune!\"";
D.q[7241] = "";
D.q[6324] = "Hello, I didn\'t feel you coming. I suppose you\'re not here to bug me, unless you\'re watching my every move. Show me your wrists, I want to see if you\'ve got tattoos.";
D.q[1551] = "Follow your friends\' advice, their experience could put an end to all your worries in the workplace.";
D.q[3937] = "Ahhh, that lazy twit Walt is finally doing a bit of work. He has to carry a load of bags of jute to the castle.";
D.q[3907] = "Hello! My name is Frost Hize. I\'m a former disciple of Xavier the Baker. Now, I\'ve got my own bakery, here, in Astrub and business is good, I can tell you!";
D.q[3941] = "Ah! I\'m glad you\'re back! So, here\'s the plan: you\'ll disguise yourself as the prince. First, find a way to pass off as a Wabbit. A potion should do. Then, go to the castle and act like you\'re the prince. Tell them that you object to the marriage or whatever. Think of something... we cannot let this wedding go ahead...";
D.q[1173] = "Yes, what do you want ?";
D.q[6459] = "I don\'t know what you\'re on about, let me in peace.";
D.q[3252] = "I don\'t know what you can expect to find in this sanctuary and this room besides certain death and the proof that the Dofus quest is beyond mere mortals like us....";
D.q[7242] = "";
D.q[5484] = "I don\'t know why this goblin loves apples so much, they\'re just full of soft little seeds! \nI like a fruit with a stone in the middle... peaches, apricots, cherries that kind of thing.";
D.q[2913] = "I don\'t like the way the Brakmarians have been acting lately. We\'re much too passive, we should attack them and conquer them once and for all. \nDid you want to tell me something?";
D.q[3959] = "Ah! At last! Give me the egg and the potion, I\'ll make sure the Prince... finds them...";
D.q[7243] = "";
D.q[7244] = "";
D.q[6478] = "Hello. Can I help you?";
D.q[4018] = "So hewe awe my men. Despite theiw weiwd faces, they\'ll do. Well, I\'ll stwoll awound this beautiful wegion a little mowe befowe going to the castle.";
D.q[6224] = "I don\'t think it\'s reasonable to talk to someone who is a complete stranger to me.";
D.q[4581] = "Hello, more haste, less speed. we haven\'t been able to flatter Elturt, but as she doesn\'t seem too belligerent there must be some way of sorting something out with her to obtain the Fogornleg Horn. We need to get to know her better, which means getting the advice of an animal specialist. There are several in Sufokia but the best suited would be Oshimo, I think. He\'s responsible for the Kennel to the north of Sufokia. Make your investigations as subtle as possible, rushing things won\'t work there either.";
D.q[5844] = "I don\'t mind if you interrupt me, so long as it\'s for a good reason.";
D.q[6181] = "Hahaha, I see you haven\'t lost your bearings. Here\'re some Kamas and a few secret old adventurer boots that might help you in battle.";
D.q[2098] = "I don\'t think you understand. Anyway... if this is your final word, I must have misjudged you...";
D.q[7245] = "";
D.q[4044] = "Oh okay. I\'ll prepare the potion right this minute then.";
D.q[1332] = "Even if it seems too easy, I\'ll have to bring myself to charge that Oni Tnec.\nNow, we must lay hands on him. I\'ll try to obtain some information about him.";
D.q[7246] = "";
D.q[1140] = "Teeheehee HEH HEH HEH HEH!\nI\'m laughing because you\'ve just lost 5 Kamas.\nTeeheehee HEH HEH HEH HEH!";
D.q[6341] = "I don\'t work any harder for Bonta than I do for anyone else. I usually help those who need my help... I\'m a softie at heart, you know. I do know that Norb, my associate who heads up the workshop to the south of Amakna, received a visit from some Bontarians recently. You should go and ask him about this.";
D.q[4166] = "All these explanations confuse me. It\'s like I\'ve always known and understood this. I feel like I\'ve locked myself into a life which isn\'t mine, which isn\'t the one I hoped for our couple. And here I\'m now. I\'ve so much to learn from her and there are so many things I want to show her... I think you\'ve made me open my eyes! I must learn how to seduce her again and win her back!";
D.q[1908] = "His name is Louc Drif, or as he calls himself, the \'independent professional delivery consultant\'. He lives in the Iop neighbourhood. If you give me your map, I\'ll write the location of his house on it. Come back to see me when you know for sure if he really is sick... or not!";
D.q[7247] = "";
D.q[7202] = "";
D.q[1416] = "I doubt the culprit\'s a militia member. Indeed, only Bontarian bakers know the Blop Gateau recipe.\nAsk Ture Inge, he certainly has documents on how to lead an investigation.";
D.q[1515] = "As long as our revenge remains unsatisfied, we\'ll keep on fighting. It\'s our duty to honour the memory of those killed in action. Once our fury extinguished, the heads will gather to declare the end of hostilities.";
D.q[7249] = "";
D.q[4025] = "I expected nothing less from you.";
D.q[1665] = "I feel an evil presence in the Dragon Pig Dungeon!";
D.q[619] = "I explained to him that this information was strictly confidential, but I also tried to imply that maybe he could do something...";
D.q[3018] = "I expected nothing less of you! Since we\'ll be talking about eternity with ghosts, your mind must be prepared. So go and meditate on the infinity of space and time next to god Xelor. His statue is within the city walls. Put a flag on the god statue on your map, this will magnetize the needle of your compass and indicate the way. Once there, have a close look at the god\'s hammer. A symbol is engraved on it. Once you\'ve seen it, come back to me.";
D.q[5968] = "I fear that the power of the Statues of Sumens may be at the height of their power.";
D.q[7250] = "";
D.q[2730] = "Everyone says those paths are twisting and the creatures which haunt them are not what we call friendly. But a Wally Elconom succeeded to draw a map. It could be useful for you to meet him. He\'s often seen round Amakna.";
D.q[4192] = "Hello adventurer! Let me welcome you aboard what\'s left of my ark! \nI used to be the captain of this ark, and in it, I would transport goods to this secret island for Otomai and his disciples. I\'ve forgotten exactly how many creatures we brought here, but there were plenty.";
D.q[1603] = "Everything\'s been said. Yet, if you have any questions, please do ask me before you go...";
D.q[4214] = "My colleagues assisted me for years in my researches, without them I\'d never have learnt nor discovered so many things. I feel like I owe them a lot for that. That\'s why I appreciate that in exchange for my potions, other adventurers help them.\nI\'d like you to help Professor Kalkulus and Stella Stukup.";
D.q[7346] = "";
D.q[7252] = "";
D.q[7251] = "";
D.q[1458] = "Cheater! Thief! Liar! I\'m gonna tell my daddy! Boooohoo!";
D.q[1179] = "There you go! You can handle a butcher\'s hatchet now. With some more practice, you\'ll even be able to slice accurately slap bang in the middle of a fight, ha-ha!\nDon\'t forget to buy yourself a hatchet to progress in your profession. I\'ll sell you one if you want...";
D.q[2463] = "I found this machine in the Sidimote Moors. It needs a special Bworker token to work.";
D.q[2797] = "I feel you want to challenge Vlad! Or maybe you just want to brave the dangers of the Damned Forest...";
D.q[5069] = "I get the feeling you\'ve come here to bring me something.. something strange.";
D.q[7347] = "";
D.q[3805] = "I got this great necklace here. It\'s magic for sure. If you get your hands on the whole set, it\'s even more powerful!";
D.q[4233] = "We find it in the pollen of the whole island, and preserve it using ice. Of course, in its primitive state, this bacteria is perfectly harmless, but through our study, we\'ve found a way to create more highly evolved strains.";
D.q[4949] = "";
D.q[921] = "Well, Go practice with Tarche for a little while. He\'s the big militiaman guarding our stock of powder. Come back when you\'re done.\n";
D.q[5055] = "What is this letter about then?\n*Reads it*\nDanathor did that? I didn\'t have any idea! Well it\'s plain to see that Danathor has gone too far this time, I;\r\n            m going to recall the troops that have started to occupy Amakna. Thank you for telling me, I will not forget your loyalty.";
D.q[4970] = "";
D.q[1472] = "A Bontarian murderer? Heheh!";
D.q[4305] = "My colleagues assisted me for many years in my researches, I\'d never have discovered so many things without them. I feel like I owe them something and I\'m glad that for my potions other adventurers can help them. \nI\'d like you to help the Professor Kalkulus, Stella Stukup, Polka Merer, and Kito.";
D.q[2390] = "Well you\'re now my apprentice. You\'ll start with small weapons, I wrote their names down in your forge\'s notebook. You\'ll need a hammer specially designed for the weapon you\'re going to forge. I\'ve all kinds of hammers if you want! Try to pick up the right one! Once you\'ll get it, you can use our work benches for forging.";
D.q[3632] = "Some day gob will come, some day he will save me.";
D.q[1112] = "I hate this town. It stinks and the people living there are so unhealthy.";
D.q[1387] = "A man in white just ran past. When he saw me, he rushed to the East.";
D.q[3924] = "A Wabbit Prince, huh? Well... Give me time to plan something...";
D.q[4744] = "Hurry up, Judge Satirev Onivin isn\'t the patient type!";
D.q[4782] = "The militia? Who do you take me for? I had no evidence and they would have dragged me off for defamation, the clowns! What do you think? They look after themselves.";
D.q[4308] = "My colleagues assisted me for many years in my researches, I\'d never have discovered so many things without them. I feel like I owe them something and I\'m glad that for my potions other adventurers can help them. \nI\'d like you to help the Professor Kalkulus, Stella Stukup, Polka Mere, Kito, the Doctor Nauh, Speet Fyer, Flip Flap, the Doctor Morose, Miss Lousy Piggy and Crocodyl Dandy.";
D.q[82] = "I\'ve been looking for a way to freeze the movement of monsters for a long, long time.";
D.q[4320] = "Not bad, swine. The jewel I\'ve on me is a fake, but you saved me the trouble of having to give out to you. \nGo back to your chief and tell him I\'ll be finished soon. One more thing, what\'s that paper that you found on one of the burglars?";
D.q[6839] = "";
D.q[1260] = "Magic poison? I\'ve no such thing!";
D.q[4399] = "The seller who\'s selling it to me? He just ran off! I think it would be a waste of time to go after him anyway... Ouassingue Juice is illegal in the city because of the smell it gives off. But otherwise it\'s not dangerous.";
D.q[6840] = "";
D.q[1164] = "What is this paper for ? A report ? For Tarazed ?_Ok, he pays me, I can fill out that...";
D.q[1268] = "Well, we\'ve a thumping problem. The shaft of the militia is blocked and I know only one man capable of clearing it quickly: you!\n\nThere is a training room in the Militia basement called \'the Scorpion Cellar\'. The aim is simple.\nSurvive the assault of 8 scorpions to finally get used to the poison and develop a Natural Defence system against its effects.\nTalk to the guard at the entry, he will let you in and give you a surprise.";
D.q[4979] = "";
D.q[3418] = "A tragic love story used to bring them into conflict as they loved the same woman. But the woman chose Yoshawa. Orukawa couldn\'t stand such an affront and attacked the woman. Yoshawa intervened and out of rage killed Orukawa suffocating him to death with a duvet made of Kirball hairs. The poor guy didn\'t even die of suffocation but of asphyxia.\nThen, Yoshawa and his lady-love decided to quit the archipelago to go to the village of Amakna.";
D.q[4110] = "What key you want me to make you honey?";
D.q[6842] = "Thanks, that\'s very kind of you. I don\'t know why, but at the moment my throat is always dry. Here, for example, I just drank a pint, and it\'s as if I didn\'t have anything to drink. With that in mind, have you got a couple of Kamas so I could buy myself another pint?";
D.q[4487] = "On the other hand I want to do you a favour, so listen up. To make Tra Khben paste, you need to crush and mix 15 Boar Snouts, 5 Greedovore Pots and 1 Quetsnakiatl Feather. If anyone asks you where you got this information, you better not tell them anything.";
D.q[6841] = "";
D.q[4727] = "The deal is done.";
D.q[2739] = "Are you looking for someone to take you away? Lucky you found me! For 100 Kamas I\'ll take you to the harbour of Madrestam. It\'s where Captain Lily keeps her boat in dry dock. A great boat and one heck of a woman! Believe me! I could easily be tempted, but you know... Unfortunately, our cultures are EX-tremely different.";
D.q[3643] = "I\'ve my own theory about many different aspects of our World. Take for example the way clouds turn upside down every second Tuesday on if the previous year has been a wet one. Or the length of Enutrof eyebrows...";
D.q[684] = "Search for an object as a symbol\nOf power, grandeur and vanity\nOf protection, such can be its role\nFrom the sea you must take it";
D.q[680] = "Do some research! That\'s part of the test. Regarding the proof you must bring back to me: don\'t damage the creation, ever! You should think about taking care of it. A piece of leather of a sword sheath, a plinth fragment of a vase... The task is difficult but not impossible. It\'s a bit like looking for a Xelor\'s clock hand in a thieving Arachnee\'s cobweb! Don\'t forget it!";
D.q[6843] = "";
D.q[4493] = "You turned the tide of the battle, but Brakmar still has the upper hand over our soldiers, but I\'m concerned that our soldiers are no match for Brakmar\'s forces. Do you think their equipment is of better quality than ours? I\'m very worried about it.";
D.q[3795] = "Come on... I\'m sure there are some people you\'d like to contact again... networking my friend, networking!";
D.q[5264] = "";
D.q[4734] = "Do you have the Hammer Hitocracy? My patience is running out... I\'m getting very... impatient.";
D.q[6844] = "Thanks, that\'s very kind of you. I don\'t know why, but at the moment my throat is always dry. Here, for example, I just drank a pint, and it\'s as if I didn\'t have anything to drink. With that in mind, have you got a couple of Kamas so I could buy myself another pint?";
D.q[2082] = "Find Nepra. You\'ll ask him some Subosycold and you\'ll bring it to Clint Pot;\r\n            he\'s an Enutrof and looks after our monsters. Don\'t pay attention to the look or the smell of the remedy, it\'s very efficient!";
D.q[5378] = "";
D.q[4972] = "That symbol... I need it! At any price! With such a plan, we can\'t fail!";
D.q[406] = "Without his pick, a miner is nothing. But remember, the pick doesn\'t make the miner. \nIn general, the best picks enable you to defend yourself against the monsters which populate the mines or against prowlers who attack the miners.\nIf you\'re looking for a pick, we can come to an arrangement. I\'ll have a little work for you to do and I\'ll give you a pick if you do a good job.";
D.q[6845] = "Thanks...hic, that\'s very kind of you. I don\'t know why, but at the moment my throat is always dry. Hic. Here, for example, I just drank a pint, and it\'s as if I didn\'t have anything to drink. With that in mind, have you...hic...got a couple of Kamas so I could buy myself another pint?";
D.q[7110] = "";
D.q[4528] = "I\'ve been told that you know how to take care of yourself. I need someone like you. You\'ve already found a better smith to supply the militia and a tactician to make the troops more focused, which is why I thought of you straight away when this came up.";
D.q[6846] = "Thanks...hic...that\'s very kind of you. I don\'t know why, but at the moment...hic...my throat is always dry. Hic. Here, for example, I just drank a pint...hic...and it\'s as if I didn\'t have anything to drink. With that in mind, have you...hic...got a couple of Kamas so I could buy myself another pint?";
D.q[7109] = "";
D.q[4537] = "Hello, I hope everything went well with Danathor. \nI need your help again, this time for a very dangerous mission. Brakmar is too quiet, and I fear they\'re planning an attack on our city in the coming days. You must retrieve their plan of attack to help us defend ourselves. Don\'t bother going to see our spy, he hasn\'t heard a thing, which worries me even more. I\'m pretty sure you\'ll find the plans in the Tower of Brakmar.";
D.q[6847] = "Thanks...hic...that\'sh very kind of yoush. I don\'t know why, but at the moment...burp...my throat ish alwaysh dry. Hic. Here, for example, I jusht drank a pint...hic...and it\'sh ash if I didn\'t have anything to drink. With that in mind, have you...hic...got a couple of Kamash so I could buy...so I could buy...erm, what wash I shaying? Oh yeah, \'ave you got two Kamas so I can...oh, never mind..";
D.q[4545] = "The assault was not entirely successful, but at least you got the best of a few of their warriors. Unfortunately I\'ve some bad news for you too. The Brakmarians found a way around Nara\'s traps and since he refused to work for them, they got rid of him. He fought the good fight and took many Brakmarians along with him to the tomb. Now we just have to find out what the Brakmarians are planning to do now.";
D.q[1957] = "Are you kidding me? This is the famous cue uttered by...heu...well, you know what I mean!";
D.q[7111] = "";
D.q[1072] = "ZZZZZzzzzz ZZZZZzzzzz";
D.q[4553] = "Why? Because I\'m not a brutish Iop or Pandawa. I\'ve more style: I make myself invisible and set numerous traps to kill Kanigers. Sometimes I make a few well-placed dagger blows, but never anything too violent. No, uncompromising violence is for brainless meatheads. Axes, swords, they\'re for brutes. Have you ever tried to use a hammer gracefully? No? Why\'s that, do you think? Because it\'s a meathead\'s weapon. Daggers, on the other hand, marry surgical precision with a ballet dancer\'s grace.";
D.q[6848] = "";
D.q[5400] = "";
D.q[6151] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[1923] = "Did you find some?";
D.q[1053] = "Are you looking for trouble or what? You obviously don\'t know my reputation..";
D.q[5052] = "";
D.q[4419] = "I have to admit, you\'ve done a great job with Xephires. Take a break - I\'ll need you again soon enough.";
D.q[7112] = "";
D.q[6850] = "";
D.q[2781] = "Are you going to bring that Dofus to Grandapan or what?";
D.q[4561] = "Greetings, I bet Oto Mustam is looking for a way to gain an advantage over us. There is a very interesting rumour that\'s been heard for some time now: a magic horn of great power is hidden somewhere. The problem is that I don\'t know from where such a rumour could come, so if you know something about it, I\'d be very interested.";
D.q[6849] = "";
D.q[7113] = "";
D.q[4959] = "I\'m still waiting for my workers.";
D.q[6122] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[6851] = "";
D.q[4585] = "Hahaha, you really gave them what for! Recover the documents and draft some fake ones, to make them think our little break-in failed. Thanks to your ingenuity everything has come up trumps. I\'m proud of you. Now we\'ve the secret documents, and those that our spy stole. It really is our lucky day!";
D.q[6852] = "";
D.q[5053] = "";
D.q[4602] = "You\'re finally here. I shall explain what the ritual involves. It\'s very simple, even a Iop can do it if he follows the instructions to the letter.\nFill the tub with Drizzle Potion, then add 10 Pandkin Seed. Plunge the object into the tub and take it out without drying it, sprinkle it with 4 measures of Magical Cure, place it in a magic breeze and the revelation will occur.\nThe tub should be heated throughout the ritual, one person should dedicate themselves to this task. Only Hornbeam Wood can be used.\nTo activate the magic breeze, use 4 Draught Potions. Again, one person should dedicate themselves to this task.\nWhen your friends are standing in front of the machines, stand in front of the tub and put the items into it in order. don\'t have any sulphur in your inventory, as you may die, or worse.";
D.q[6153] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[7129] = "";
D.q[7114] = "";
D.q[4837] = "";
D.q[1651] = "On which creature do you want me to take a divinatory look?";
D.q[4922] = "*blushes* It would be a pleasure but I have a lot tiring work to do right now. I promise that we will have another opportunity when I\'m not as busy.";
D.q[7116] = "";
D.q[4658] = "The Bontarian spy gave up without a fight? Well, you\'re starting to get a reputation for yourself in Bonta, it seems.\nDid you think to give false documents to our enemies? Yes? Excellent, everything is taking place as planned. Grab a quick rest, I\'ll need you for the next part .";
